# Context Framework

This project maintains a set of context documents in `memory/` that capture key decisions, standards, and architecture. Read these files at the start of any planning or implementation task to ensure responses are grounded in project reality.

## Memory Files

| File | Purpose | When to read |
|------|---------|--------------|
| `memory/ABOUT.md` | Project vision, objectives, and guiding principles | Planning, scoping, prioritization |
| `memory/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Tech stack, project structure, API surface, database schema | Design decisions, new features, structural changes |
| `memory/TECHNICAL.md` | Naming conventions, coding patterns, error handling, linting/formatting | Writing or reviewing code |
| `memory/TESTING.md` | Test tooling, structure, mocking strategies, known gaps | Writing or reviewing tests |
| `memory/SETUP.md` | Prerequisites, database setup, how to run the app | Environment or setup questions |
| `memory/ENV_SCRIPTS.md` | Environments, env vars (e.g. `.env`), and developer scripts/commands | Setup, running commands, or when to go off-script |
| `memory/WORKFLOW_STATUS.md` | Process stages, work item structure, acceptance criteria, status location, build/test protocol | Starting work, tracking status, transitioning stages, or defining stories |

## How to use

- Before planning or making changes, read the relevant memory files listed above.
- When the user asks you to "update memory" or "remember this", update the appropriate memory file with the new information.
- Prefer precise, actionable content over verbose descriptions when updating memory files.
